  "text": "At the same time, a separate body of literature in psychology reports that intellectual capital is an important ingredient in economic development [CITATION_1] and has direct positive implications for life satisfaction [CITATION_2] . For example, [CITATION_3] reported that general intelligence in childhood is positively associated with the life-course stability of happiness. In a similar vein, [CITATION_4] , using data from 81 countries and 50 US states, showed that intelligence leads to a more equal distribution of 2 We use \"life satisfaction\" and \"subjective wellbeing\" (SWB) interchangeably throughout the paper.",
